Some Pre-Work for this includes&#58;

1) Make sure the OS on meshconfig(-itb).grid.iu.edu is up-to-date (RHEL7). And remove all current (old) MCA components (it might be best to wipe the current instances and start over with fresh VM instance)

2) Install docker-engine from upstream docker repo (not from epel - uninstall the epel one if it&#39;s already installed). Here is the installation guide &#62; <a href='https&#58;//docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/rhel/' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/rhel/</a>   You may also need to update /var/lib/docker with /usr/local/docker

3) Remove apache and install nginx (from epel). We will need to work on the configuration file for nginx, but documentation will be made as we move along.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='31359#1479154660'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-11-14T20:17:40+00:00">Nov 14, 2016 08:17 PM UTC</time> by <b>Christopher Pipes</b><a class="anchor" name="1479154660">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>I&#39;m working with Tom and Soichi to get a Cert for this now, I&#39;ll update this again once I know more.

