by /DC=ch/DC=cern/OU=Organic Units/OU=Users/CN=mckee/CN=500323/CN=Shawn Mc Kee</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='31359#1475256509'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-09-30T17:28:29+00:00">Sep 30, 2016 05:28 PM UTC</time> by <b>Soichi Hayashi</b><a class="anchor" name="1475256509">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Chris,

gocdb2sls service is not running on meshconfig.grid.iu.edu. This is a OSG/WLCG specific component so it doesn&#39;t come with MCA. You will have to install it manually along with a private LS instance (there are docker containers for both).

Meanwhile, there is no such thing as oim2sls service. There aren&#39;t that many purely OSG sites, and also most of them are already registered to global LS, so I am not sure if you really need oim2sls service.

Soichi</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='31359#1475254961'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2016-09-30T17:02:41+00:00">Sep 30, 2016 05:02 PM UTC</time> by <b>Christopher Pipes</b><a class="anchor" name="1475254961">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>I&#39;ve pinged Soichi about this.

